cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques for improving face recognition and hallucination. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network architecture for face hallucination, which falls under the category of deep learning (DL) and ML. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) for face hallucination, which is a popular technique in the field of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. The paper also involves image processing and manipulation, which falls under the category of multimedia (MM). Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training the face recognition and GAN-based DSNet jointly, which involves optimization and training of neural networks. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category.
